The course covers the following topics: the links between stress, emotions, sleep, exercise, nutrition and social relationships with mental health; problem-solving and emotion regulation skills, opportunities to get help.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to raise awareness of mental health and to develop the skills necessary to cope with one's own mental health.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student notices his/her mental health situation, understands different ways to increase his/her well-being, knows several self-help techniques, and knows where to ask for help.
